THE  COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92 of 15 June 1992 concerning specific measures for Madeira with regard to certain agricultural products (1), and in particular Article 10 thereof,
Whereas, for the purposes of Article 2 of Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92, the specific supply balance should be drawn up for the 1992/93 marketing year for certain vegetable oils benefiting from the exemption scheme for duties on direct imports from third  countries or from aid on consignments from the rest of the Community;
